Identifying a problem. Describing the problem. Collecting the information needed to solve the problem. Analysing the problem. Solving the problem and making propositions. The problem-based learning method is applied.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give students the opportunity to solve an economic problem in a specific organisation by using the knowledge and skills learned throughout different courses and to associate theory with practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) is able to identify and describe an economic problem; 2) is able to find the information needed to solve the problem; 3) is able to apply previously learned knowledge to solve the problem; 4) is able to conduct empirical analysis, draw conclusions and make propositions.
